{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_73","type":"agent_message","text":"The `XmlConfiguration` decompile made the root cause clear: its string constructor always prepends a `DOCTYPE` pointing at `http://jetty.mortbay.org/configure_1_2.dtd`, and `initParser()` is supposed to redirect that to the packaged `org/mortbay/xml/configure_6_0.dtd`. That means the remaining native failure is still a resource-registration gap, not a need to enable `http:`. I’m waiting for the trace run to finish, then I’ll register that local XML DTD resource and rerun the targeted test."}}
